thread.title: Listen: Songs about celebrities

author: Cox Media Group National Content Desk
title: Listen: Songs about celebrities
text:
Fall Out Boy dominated airwaves with their sonnet "Uma Thurman" this summer.
It made us curious: What other hit songs have been named after celebrities and prominent figures? As it turns out, there are a couple.
Weezer - Buddy Holly
Mika - Grace Kelly
Jay Z - Tom Ford
Bree Sharp - David Duchovny
Gorillaz - Clint Eastwood
Pharrell - Marilyn Monroe
OutKast - Rosa Parks
and even though the person wasn't real, the song took on a life of its own after this landmark moment (3:38) in entertainment:
Michael Jackson - Billie Jean
